Chris Robshaw and his England teammates will be on course for a multi-million pound payday if they beat Ireland in Dublin on Sunday to maintain their Six Nations winning streak.

A huge new deal was brokered with the RFU in 2013 which will see the squad share £7.5million if they win the Grand Slam and follow it up with victory at the World Cup.

The deal was delivered in an attempt to avert a repeat of the pay dispute before the 2011 World Cup, when England’s players threatened to boycott a dinner held by sponsors O2.

