Each player receives £15,000 per appearance, not allowing for win bonuses, with an ever-present in the Six Nations squad guaranteed £75,000, but with a Grand Slam bonus of £25,000 per player, victory today would leave England needing two more wins to secure a six-figure pay-out.

An RFU bonus worth £5m is likely to be shared by the 30-man squad if Stuart Lancaster guides his side to victory in the World Cup on home soil. That is double the amount on offer for winning the 2011 event in New Zealand.

