‘You don’t talk about it,’ he said. ‘You just focus on what they need to do to be better players. It is a very good environment Stuart Lancaster has created with England.

‘The players enjoy it and they really enjoy the brand of rugby as well. They are learning every day. That’s what it is all about in international rugby.

‘We are developing nicely. We are on the right track and the Ireland game is another stepping stone to where this team wants to go or what English rugby wants to do.’

